import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd
def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['age'] = pd.to_datetime(data['age'], format='%Y-%m-%d', errors='coerce').dt.year
    plt.hist(data['age'], bins=20, color='blue', edgecolor='black')
    plt.axvline(data['age'].median(), color='red', linestyle='dashed', linewidth=1, label=f'Median Age: {data["age"].median():.2f}')
    plt.legend()
    plt.title('What is the age distribution of the people in the dataset?', wrap=True)
    plt.xlabel('Age')
    plt.ylabel('Frequency')
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    gender_counts = data['gender'].value_counts()
    plt.bar(gender_counts.index, gender_counts.values)
    plt.title('What is the gender distribution of the people in the dataset?', wrap=True)
    return plt

chart = plot(data)

import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd
def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    education_levels = data['education'].value_counts()
    plt.pie(education_levels, labels=education_levels.index, autopct='%1.1f%%')
    plt.title('What is the distribution of education levels among the people in the dataset?', wrap=True)
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['income'] = pd.to_numeric(data['income'], errors='coerce')
    fig, ax = plt.subplots(figsize=(10, 6))
    ax.boxplot(data['income'], vert=False, showmeans=True, meanline=True, labels=['Income'])
    ax.set_xlabel('Income')
    ax.set_title('What is the distribution of income levels among the people in the dataset?')
    ax.axvline(data['income'].median(), color='r', linestyle='--', label=f'Median: {data["income"].median():,.2f}')
    ax.legend()
    return plt

chart = plot(data)

import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['age'] = pd.to_numeric(data['age'], errors='coerce')
    data['income'] = pd.to_numeric(data['income'], errors='coerce')
    plt.scatter(data['age'], data['income'])
    plt.title('What is the relationship between age and income among the people in the dataset?', wrap=True)
    plt.xlabel('Age')
    plt.ylabel('Income')
    return plt

chart = plot(data)
